        boolean isCloudy = true;
        boolean willRain = isCloudy && Math.random() > 0.5;
        boolean hasUmbrella = willRain && Math.random() > 0.3;
        System.out.println("Is it necessary to carry an umbrella? " + hasUmbrella);
    }
}",

If an intervention ensures it is sunny, will this change the necessity of carrying an umbrella?
